ABOUT US
Building The Future Of Work
Read AI is building the future of work, where every interaction is improved with AI.
Get started
MEETINGS
AI-generated summaries, transcripts, and video highlights to make your meetings more efficient, effective, and valuable.
EMAIL
Automated summaries, Q&A, and action items generated from your Gmail and Outlook inbox with Read's Productivity AI.
MESSAGING
Automated summaries, Q&A, and action items generated across your Teams and Slack messages with Read’s Productivity AI.
SCHEDULING & MORE
Go beyond better meetings with Read Smart Scheduler, workflow integrations, and so much more!
Our Story
Productivity AI automates the mundane in meetings, scheduling, email, and messages to centralize and simplify your knowledge sources. Read AI is set to be the independent system of record for productivity AI where people attend fewer meetings, send less emails, read fewer messages, and decisions are as simple as swiping right.
Executive Team
Based out of Seattle, WA, Read AI was founded in 2021 by David Shim, Robert Williams, Elliott Waldron and backed by Madrona Venture Group and Goodwater. The team has founded and led companies that, to date, have generated hundreds of millions in revenue and billions in market valuation across Foursquare, Snapchat, Placed, and Farecast.
David Shim
CO-FOUNDER, CEO
Former CEO of Foursquare, Founder and CEO of Placed (sold to Snapchat in 2017).
Rob Williams
CO-FOUNDER, CTO
Former Senior Director of Engineering at Foursquare and Placed.
Elliott Waldron
CO-FOUNDER, VP OF DATA SCIENCE
Former VP of Data Science at Foursquare and Placed.
Investors
Supported by
Smash Capital’s partnership is grounded in decades of shared history at the highest level of asset management, software, internet, media, and entertainment. Together we have a proven history of global success as both investors and operators of multi-billion-dollar franchises.

Smash Capital focuses on investing in growth stage technology companies that are redefining their markets. These companies are capable of building large, emotionally resonant brands with their customers. The firm’s history in scaling and cementing brands uniquely positions the firm to help investments scale up behind this potential.
Brad Twohig
CO-FOUNDER AND MANAGING PARTNER AT SMASH CAPITAL
“Productivity is set to be one of the largest opportunities for AI in 2025. Read AI is the preferred meeting notes solution for millions of users and is poised to bring broader productivity AI to the global masses.”
Goodwater’s mission is to empower exceptional entrepreneurs everywhere to change the world for good. We are the world’s largest venture capital fund exclusively focused on consumer technology, with over 80 venture and growth investments and over 600 seed deals across more than 50 countries.

Our consumer-only sector focus enables a systematic global approach, and our proprietary software platform helps us to identify and support the best consumer tech companies in all corners of the globe.
Coddy Johnson
PARTNER AT GOODWATER CAPITAL, BOARD MEMBER AT READ AI
“Read AI empowers every knowledge worker to spend radically less time on process - meetings, emails, and messaging - and more time on what matters most: creating value.”
Madrona is a venture capital firm based in Seattle with an office in Palo Alto. With nearly 30 years of investing in early-stage technology companies, the firm has worked with founders from day one to help build their company for the long run.

Madrona invests predominantly in seed and Series A rounds of companies in the Pacific NW building across the information technology spectrum and in Acceleration (B and beyond) stage companies building with AI, regardless of geography. The firm has more than $3 billion under management. Madrona was an early investor in companies such as Amazon, Snowflake, UIPath, Smartsheet, Rover, and Redfin.
Matt McIlwain
MANAGING DIRECTOR AT MADRONA, BOARD MEMBER AT READ AI
“Rather than a co-pilot, Read is building an AI auto-pilot to improve knowledge workers' individual and team effectiveness across meetings, emails, and messages."
Our Stance on Climate and AI
We believe it is our responsibility to operate sustainably and contribute to the global effort against climate change.

We know that AI is some of the most energy-intensive technologies in the world and we are committed to measuring and limiting the environmental impact of our organization whenever possible.
Data-driven Decision Making: We are committed to measuring our energy consumption and carbon emissions to inform our roadmap and larger business initiatives.
Intentional Efficiency: We strive to optimize our operations for energy efficiency and minimize carbon emissions.
Proactive Innovation: We will explore and implement forward-thinking practices while sharing our learnings with the broader community.
Empower Our Customers: We are dedicated to enabling and supporting our customers in their own sustainability journey.

<script>
  // Based on https://discourse.webflow.com/t/detect-browser-language-and-redirect-but-allow-switch-language/250255/13

  const WEBFLOW_LANGUAGE_COOKIE_KEY = "webflow_language";
  const SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES = ["es", "it", "pt", "fr", "ja"];

  function getWebflowLanguageCookie() {
    const cookies = document.cookie.split(";").reduce((acc, cookieString) => {
      const [name, value] = cookieString.split("=");
      acc[name.trim()] = value;
      return acc;
    }, {});

    return cookies[WEBFLOW_LANGUAGE_COOKIE_KEY];
  }

  function setWebflowLanguageCookie(lang) {
    document.cookie = `${WEBFLOW_LANGUAGE_COOKIE_KEY}=${lang}; path=/; max-age=31536000; domain=.read.ai`;
  }

  // This event listener waits for the DOM to be fully loaded before executing the code
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
    // Check if the user's preferred language is already set
    const userLangPreference = getWebflowLanguageCookie();

    // If the userLangPreference is not set, detect the browser language and set it
    if (!userLangPreference) {
      const fullUserLang = navigator.language || navigator.userLanguage;

      if (!fullUserLang) {
        setWebflowLanguageCookie("en");
      } else {
        const userLang = fullUserLang.split("-")[0]; // match any locale such as en-US, es-ES, etc.

        if (SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES.includes(userLang)) {
          setWebflowLanguageCookie(userLang);
        } else {
          setWebflowLanguageCookie("en");
        }
      }
    }

    // Redirect the user to the appropriate language version if needed
    const currentLang = getWebflowLanguageCookie();

    if (
      SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES.includes(currentLang) &&
      !window.location.pathname.startsWith(`/${currentLang}`)
    ) {
      window.location.replace(`/${currentLang}`);
    }

    // Function to switch the language
    function switchLanguage(lang) {
      setWebflowLanguageCookie(lang);
    }

    // Enable locale switcher to set the locale storage value
    const desktopLocaleButtons = document.querySelectorAll(
      ".locales-wrapper-desktop a.navbar__menu__link"
    );
    const mobileLocaleButtons = document.querySelectorAll(
      ".locales-wrapper-mobile a.navbar__menu__link"
    );

    const attachSwitchLanguageToButton = function (button) {
      const lang = button.getAttribute("hreflang"); // will be 'en', 'es', etc.

      button.addEventListener("click", function () {
        switchLanguage(lang);
      });
    };

    // Attach a click event listener to the buttons
    desktopLocaleButtons.forEach(attachSwitchLanguageToButton);

    mobileLocaleButtons.forEach(attachSwitchLanguageToButton);
